Šimon Ornest: In our concerts we want to accumulate positive energy
It is said that in less than a month the end of the world will come, what do you think about it?
It's just one of so many alarming news that we like to grab.
The Tap Tap music group we rather like to joke about this and we like to say that we are the only music group in the world that manages to bring up enough positive energy to postpone the end of the world or to avoid it.
In addition, in December you organize a really original project: three concerts against the end of the world.
Can you explain it to our readers?
This is a state-of-the-art beneficial act that we have been planning for two years.
We decided to take advantage of the marketing potential that has the end of the Mayan calendar set for December 21 at 11:10.
The day before, on December 20 at 21:00, we will organize 3 simultaneous concerts in Prague, Brno and Ostrava.
They will end approximately at the same time when the Maya calendar ends on Kiribati Island, in the Pacific Ocean, 12 hours ahead of our time zone.
Who did this idea come up with?
Initially it was my idea, then we were all forging the project together with our designer Honza Augusta.
In addition to wishing to gather enough positive energy and avoid the end of the world, we also want to reflect, together with society, on the state in which we will leave the world to our children.
On the occasion of the end of the Mayan calendar we have also created a unique collection of articles: boots, shirts, bags and original keychains against the end of the world that can be purchased at www.e-tap.cz, another way to support us.
The group The Tap Tap, along with other interpreters, also sang the so-called hymn against the end of the world, which is titled "The end of the world, canceled."
Currently it is very popular on YouTube, can you hear it in beneficial concerts?
Of course yes, and it will be just the last, well, as long as everything goes well and the world doesn't end...
All interpreters will sing at the same time in all three concerts.
The hymns will simultaneously link to each other thanks to the special live broadcast on the Czech TV.
Tomáš Hanák has written the letter of this song and plays the protagonist role of Jesus in the videoclip, where she also sings Xindl X.
How did this collaboration emerge?
We work together even with other personalities from the Czech cultural scene, apart from organizing many beneficial events and concerts...
We put our entire efforts to participate in this project.
It has been shown that most of them are interested and have fun to work with us.
What will the money collected in the concerts against the end of the world be allocated to?
The equipment for the educational center without barriers Studeo, which we completed in its sixth consecutive year with the civil association Tap in Jedličkov ústav.
Students at Jedličkův ústav school regularly receive the visit of teachers with whom they perform fun and interesting activities.
Students do not have enough economic means to pay for teachers and we make an effort to make it possible.
In the framework of the completion of the works in Jedličkův ústav, there will be an independent building to which we will move with this project.
In each concert there are several groups and interpreters.
What are the selection criteria?
We attempt to develop a program that will be attractive for all generations, including children.
For example, in Prague, Chinaski, Support Lesbians, Illustratosphere with Dan Bárta, The Tap Tap, Marián Bango and Jiří Suchý.
For more detailed information, see www.kpks.cz.
Have you planned another similar “spectacular action” in the future?
In May we will perform for the first time at the Pražské jaro festival, so here we will surely prepare an attractive program with interesting guests.
Next year we would also like to play at the Bohemian National Hall in New York and me personally, taking advantage of that we are in the United States, I would like to complete it with performances in Washington and Chicago.
Your plans abroad are not precisely minimalist, so far you have acted for example in Madrid, Brussels, London or Moscow.
The Tap Tap is, however, a group made up of people with disabilities.
What is the logistics and organization of these trips?
It’s not so difficult how it can look at first sight.
There are five members in electric wheelchair, the chairs must travel in the luggage compartment and we also carry a lot of weight, the boxes with the instruments...
However, so far we have arranged it well. ČSA and British Airways were perfectly prepared, which is no longer surprising me.
Even in Moscow, from which we have returned recently, everything went out without trouble.
Thanks to exit abroad you can compare the different attitudes of society towards the disabled and other aspects.
What have you met with so far?
In Madrid, Luxembourg, London and other cities, everything works better than here; in Russia we have witnessed that, in the east, there is a lot of way to go.
Unlike Prague, Moscow is full of barriers, there is still not frequent that a person moves alone through the city center in an electric wheelchair.
Something as common as it is, for example, to give preference to someone in wheelchair in elevator, there is not.
Fortunately, a civilian association has been established that strives to thematic the problems of persons with disabilities.
In what aspects should we take an example of more advanced countries?
There are many aspects in which we go behind...
But it is important to mention that the improvement and improvement of the situation always depends on the people you directly affect.
In London and Madrid, it is very normal for people with a serious disability to move in public on their own and can go to the service, the museum, wherever they want.
But it’s not very common for a large number of people with disabilities to actively participate in social life, in this aspect, with The Tap Tap, let’s go a little ahead!
A respectful or barrier-free society is one thing, but when it comes to the time that eminent athletes, artists, actors, politicians or lawyers arise, it will begin to really change everything.
So far, they are isolated cases of people who have a great will.
The The Tap Tap group is currently very popular, but if we looked at a few years ago, what led you to form the group in 1998?
I entered as an educator at Jedličkov ústav, where there were a lot of young people around me who wanted to devote themselves to something.
And since I am a musician, I play, among others, the saxophon, I founded an amateur group with a workmate.
And over time, as our moderator Láđa Angelovič says, we got a little bit of our hands (laughs).
However, popularity has not come until the last few years, or am I wrong?
It is true that helped us a lot to connect with famous singers and also work actively to promote the group.
We come to the conclusion that the work you don’t see is as if it didn’t exist.
Thanks to the aid of the European Union, we can also allow ourselves to teach quality, equipment, etc.
Did you want to get so far away with The Tap Tap?
From the beginning I saw the potential there was, that something can be done otherwise.
The world of the show is full of things that resemble each other.
It is logical, in its own way, everything new is welcomed with caution and it takes a long time to accept itself.
There are few extraordinary things, but I dare to say that The Tap Tap is one of them.
The impression of someone who sees us for the first time is clearly compassion, it is a natural reaction.
But compassion is entirely superfluous because people with disabilities are not abandoned beings who suffer and whom we should have compassion.
There are people who are able to live a full life and develop, with the condition, of course, that they have the necessary means.
I always say that if something goes well to people with disabilities, then it is not just an advance for them, but for the whole society.
Did you help the fact that you are a demanding boss, as many people describe?
